[49m[39m  496, 496[0m:[39m[49m One more thing: the 75% utilization target that every hospital uses as a benchmark is somewhat arbitrary. The "right" utilization depends on your case mix, turnover times, and tolerance for overtime. A 90% utilized OR with frequent overtime cases is not better than a 75% utilized OR that finishes on time every day. Include a utilization ceiling in your constraints, not just a floor.
[0m[49m[39m  497, 497[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **What's still missing for production:**
